reviews.review_text: winterland i think i've given up on rateing the shows.  even on a bad night the dead were good.  so... the only thing to do is rate the recording.  very nicely recorded -  thank you.

BEST Crazy Fingers Out of all 144 times the band played "Crazy Fingers," this one is still my favorite. I always love when Keith breaks out the Fender Rhodes. Absolutely beautiful vocals from Jerry, and very unique and punctuated rhythm from Bobby on his first Ibanez custom. Great show all around from the hiatus year. Classic AUD.

Blues For Allah What a great song, it is inspiring. The songs from this album all have this mysterious sound to them like a middle eastern sound maybe hence; Allah, King Solomen, Arabian winds ,the Allahmbra, the Pyramids. The songs are rich and full of the mysteries of man and life.
